title: For Sale:  Paracord 550 Adjustable Survival Rifle Sling Strap For AR15 AK47 SKS
postcontent:
Custom made black adjustable paracord 550 parachute cord survival rifle Sling. Adjustable from 22" to 44" inches in length. The Universal nylon ends will fit almost any rifle. Will fit most tactical rifles. Some hunting rifles have a quick detach swivel stud, (see pictures above). For those rifles you might need to purchase a set of quick detach swivels to attach this sling. The nylon will also not scratch your gun like the steel clips will. The ends are made of 1" wide 4200lb tensile strength nylon. You could pull a truck with this stuff. I use the nylon instead of leather for the added strength and will not get brittle like leather over time. The nylon is held together with a black 1/4" chicago screw. The black finish on the screws are highly scratch resistant, seems to be a black chrome finish. Made of new USA made Mil spec government approved 550 7 strand Paracord. There is a total of about 50 feet of paracord in this sling. In an emergency you can unravel the outer 25 feet of cord and still have a useful black sling. 

The USA made paracord is manufactured to Mil-C-5040H Type III standards. This paracord has seven removable inner strands. Each of the 7 strands of 100% nylon strands are made from two-ply yarns. This is certainly not the lower quality paracord that is made from bulk fibers. Each of these 7 strands are capable of holding 50 pounds. The outer cord is made from 32 strands which are braided together and can hold 200 pounds. Add it up (50x7 + 200) and the cord can hold 550 lbs, therefore it is truly 550 paracord. 
Paracord is like duck tape and has unlimited uses only limited by your imagination. The 7 inner strands can also be removed and used for things like fishing line, or sewing thread.


I usually sell them for $50, but they are now just $25. Shipping is free. I take Pay-pal or can meet in Shelbyville KY.

title: For Sale:  TIPS for Scam Detection
postcontent:
There are some excellent scammers out there that use ‘trickery’ to deceive you into thinking you can buy this great deal (Too good to be true prices) weapon, but the catch is….”Send to your FFL info” etc. You will never meet them FTF they just want your check.

When looking at an item in the left hand column it says ‘Price’: then it says ‘Seller’ (private usually). Under ‘Seller’ in royal blue it says “Listings by this user.” When you hit that, the scammers other items for sale will pop up. One scammer that tends to use ‘Jacksonville’ as his location currently has 14 items for sale. He is very clever in that he changes the backdrop colors (some blue, red, white, military canvass etc) and his print type will change etc. He creates this illusion to deceive you, the would be buyer, that there are many different guns for sale by many different sellers. Just for fun ‘search’ Ruger SR-556. Hit Listings by this user  on some of the newest ones. He has two SR-556’s you will see what I am talking about, but maybe he will pull his ad and move on to Idaho ‘Armslist.’

Bottom line, when someone will ONLY SHIP and not meet face to face or provide info they will be a scam. Don’t send money to anyone unless of course, a dealer.

I hope this helps someone (and no, I did not get ripped off, just passing along info).

title: For Sale:  Dillon Square Deal Progressive Machine
postcontent:
Dillon Square Deal – Compact Progressive Reloading Machine

This setup is in good condition and works great.  Remarkably faster than any standard reloading press, and easy to use (but not as easy to set up).  More information is readily available on the Dillon website, including a demonstration video.  It really is that easy to use.  These Square Deal presses are also covered by Dillon’s “No BS” warranty, which provides lifetime warranty protection.  Dillon will even rebuild the machine upon request and without charge (except for shipping).  I’m not sure why that would ever be needed as it is very well built and I don’t see anything that would wear out except maybe in commercial use.

This is the solution to these repeated shortages of pistol ammunition.  It is much cheaper to stockpile primers and powder than it is ammunition.  Bullets always seem to be available, although delivery times are currently slow.

I have the press, with the standard auto powder and auto primer accessories.  It also has a low primer alert and a nice custom knob on the powder measure, which is a big improvement when using the press.

I am selling it set up to run one cartridge.  I have dies and tool heads for .38 Special, 357 Magnum, 9mm, and .45 acp.  Your choice on what you want set up in the press.  I will also provide a free Lee powder scale if you don’t already have one.

I will also be selling the extra dies and tool heads and whoever buys the press will have first choice.  Although it is obviously possible to change the dies in a tool head, but having everything set up in its own tool head greatly facilitates changing the reloading machine to a different caliber.

The only reason I am replacing this machine is that I also want to be able to reload rifle cartridges with the same kind of Dillon setup.  The Square Deal press will only reload straight wall pistol cases.

I am asking $350 for the press and related equipment with everything required to load one of the above listed cartridges.  I’m sure this seems high compared to simply ordering a new one, but Dillon is currently running a 6 to 8 week backlog and that is impacting prices.  $350 is a pretty average current sell price on Ebay.  If I don’t sell it in the next week or so, I will just list it on Ebay.

I will sell any remaining toolhead/die sets for the current Dillon delivered price ($133.39) as soon as the press is sold.  Your advantage is no 6 to 8 week wait, and everything is already installed in the tool head and ready to run.

Call me at REDACTED or email me at REDACTED   I am located in Colorado City (about 25 miles south of Pueblo).  I will be in Denver on May 22 and could deliver the press to the metro area, but would much prefer to have the new owner pick it up here so I can go through the operation of the press with them.

The Guardian 22 the goal was simple - create a great quality suppressor with best-in-class suppression that could be purchased for the price of a tax stamp. You could spend hundreds more for another .22 suppressor, but ask your self one question - why? Whether you are looking for outstanding suppression, safety, multi-caliber usage, upgradability, weight, length, longevity, or price, the Guardian 22 has it all.

Suppression:
The Guardian 22 compares favorably to suppressors costing twice as much on the market today, demonstrating our commitment to provide the best sound suppression possible. The Guardian utilizes K baffle technology, a tried and true baffle technology used in the quietest suppressors available.

Maintenance:
Just because you can take a suppressor apart when it's clean doesn't make it user serviceable. How many manufacturers claim to have user serviceable suppressors, but when you use it you find out their claims are just that - claims. Their special tools break, don't work, or you didn't buy them because they wanted an extra $50. Even if the tool worked, you can't get the suppressor apart to clean it yourself, after as few as a couple hundred rounds fired. And as with all Huntertown Arms suppressors, all it takes to remove your end caps is a standard, box end, or crescent wrench, a bench vise, pair of pliers, or any other tool that can grab a standard socket. No special tools required. Ever.

Longevity:
There are several features designed into the Guardian 22 to ensure safe and enjoyable use beyond a lifetime. Most bullet strikes on a suppressor occur on the end cap. Our end caps are made of softer aluminum so that if there is an end cap strike, the end cap will give way causing minimal if any damage to the rest of your Guardian 22 suppressor. The affected end cap, and any damaged baffles can be easily replaced without having to replace the entire core.

Upgradability:
The Guardian 22 shares the same dimensions as our Kestrel 22, a premium level, heavy duty suppressor providing best in class suppression along with unparrelled maintainence and longevity options. Your Guardian 22 can be upgraded at any time to use the Kestrel core, giving you a path to to most capable rimfire suppressor we offer.

title: For Sale:  Silencer/Supressor 556 .223
postcontent:
User serviceable centerfire rifle suppressors have been longer and heavier than their sealed counterparts. That's changed with the introduction of the Kestrel 5.56. Engineered from the ground up to maximize serviceability while not compromising on weight, length, or strength, the Kestrel 556 provides the most user friendly centerfire rifle suppressor in existence. Whether you are looking for outstanding suppression, safety, ease of maintenance, weight, length, longevity, or price, the Kestrel 5.56 has the features you are looking for.

Suppression:
The Kestrel 5.56 had one goal - provide a hearing safe centerfire rifle suppressor that can be easily maintained and repaired. It does not disappoint.

Maintenance:
Cleaning the Kestrel 5.56 is a breeze. Centerfire rifle suppressors need to be cleaned and inspected, just like rimfire suppressors. With the Kestrel 5.56 full user servicability is truely a reality. The Kestrel core is constructed of stainless steel for superior cleanability. You can use chemical solutions safe to stainless steel but that remove nasty lead deposits (the "Dip"). The core breaks down so that you can put it into a reloading tumbler, or use a bead blaster for fast and efficient cleaning. And unlike other monocore technologies, you can dip your Kestrel core without worrying about damaging the exposed finish on your core.

Kestrel baffles are fully encased for superior strength and to prevent lead and carbon buildup between the core and the tube, even after thousands of rounds fired. This provides for quick and easy removal of your Kestrel core, without the hassle or need of pushers or other devices to remove it. And as with all Huntertown Arms suppressors, all it takes to remove your end caps is a standard, box end, or crescent wrench, a bench vise, pair of pliers, or any other tool that can grab a standard socket. No special tools required. Ever.

Longevity:
There are several features designed into the Kestrel to ensure your safe and enjoyable use of the Kestrel beyond a lifetime. Most bullet strikes on a suppressor occur on the end cap. The Kestrel design separates the end cap from the registered part so that if there is an end cap strike it will be more likely your suppressor can be repaired or replaced without having to replace the registered part.

We are huge proponents of stacked bafle technology for another reason. With a monocore, there is only one blast baffle. When that blast baffle erodes, the core has to be replaced. This may or may not be a warranty repair, but in any event you have lost the use of your suppressor while it is at the manufacturer for repair.

Kestrel core baffles should be rotated (like tires) whenever the core is cleaned. With four baffles available to act as blast baffles, the Kestrel will allow up to five times the number of rounds fired before re-coring.

Safety:
The Kestrel core is fully encased in an inner stainless steel wall. In the event of an internal baffle strike, the inner core is strong enough to capture the damaged projectile and baffle material, protecting the tube as much as possible against catastrophic failure.
